    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for high offensive output today, anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (85.90) and **Gunnar Henderson** (81.76). **Kyle Tucker** remains our most reliable asset, benefiting from a prime matchup against Ryan Feltner in a hitter-friendly environment that inflates his base projection by 14%. While **Gunnar Henderson** faces a 31% rain risk, his leadoff spot and favorable platoon matchup against Gavin Williams make him nearly mandatory despite the weather cloud. We are also aggressively targeting speed-focused matchups; **Josh Lowe** and **Andy Pages** are both starts today, as their ability to exploit Ryan Feltner\u2019s slow delivery\u2014combined with the favorable park factors\u2014elevates their production potential well into the \"Strong\" tier. \n\nThe primary lineup construction challenge today involved **Nasim Nunez**, who narrowly missed the cut with a 57.95 score. While **Nasim Nunez** provides the elite stolen base upside we crave, his projected placement at the bottom of the order and the tactical efficiency of our current starters, particularly the multi-category upside of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66) and **Jacob Wilson** (67.97), forced him to the bench. Meanwhile, **Drake Baldwin** faces a tougher test against Cristopher S\u00e1nchez, resulting in a marginal 48.10 score; he stays in the lineup solely due to the scarcity of the catcher position, though he remains a candidate to watch if lineup adjustments deviate from our projections. We are proceeding with this configuration to balance our 5x5 Roto needs, keeping **Marcell Ozuna** and **Coby Mayo** in reserve to protect our limited game caps should the weather turn in Cleveland or the lineup cards shift unexpectedly.",
